subSubSection.paragraph:
Female thalli with conical or elongate-oblong primary appendage, having a ± pointed and inwardly curved apex. Perithecium ovoid, showing one strongly convex side whereas the opposite side is straight to slightly concave. [Detailed descriptions: 
Thaxter 1908
; 
Majewski 1994b
; 
Santamaria 2002
; 
Santamaria 2003
]

Widespread and known from all continents except Oceania. Occurs on
Anthicus Paykull, 1798
and allied genera (Col. Anthicidae ) ( Santamaria 2002 ; Majewski 2008 ;
Bernardi et al. 2014
). Also in Korea (
Lee et al. 2011
).
